            GET Requests (i want something) 
            
                 Client takes <- from the Server
                 
            
            POST Requests (i give something)
            
                 Submit Button for POST Requests
                 
                 Client posts -> to the Server
                 
               ASYNCH Requests 
              
                 will delete for example just in the backend (behind the scenes), but will not extra refresh the website to see the changes
                 
                 async await is OPTIONAL -> its doing the same like promises then and catch
                 
                 
                 
            RELATIVE PATH
            
                is looking for the file in the current directory/folder
            
            
            
            STRICT PATH ?
            
                is looking fir the file whereever it is     we have to use __dirname (directory name)
                
                
                
            API
            
                endpoint:            starting url                                                  https://......
                path:                for specific type of data (like a filter for the json data)   https://....../.../.../...
                parameters:          for specific type of data (like a filter for the json data)   https://....../.../.../...
                authentication:      companies use this for example to -> limit the access to the api they offer
            
            
            
            JSON data (Javascript Object Notation)
            
                we got json data if we are using an API
                
                Syntax:
                
                            {
                            "tasks": [
                            {
                              "id": "1",
                              "text": "learn programming",
                              "day": "everyday"
                            },
                            {
                              "id": "2",
                              "text": "working",
                              "day": "weekdays"
                            }
                          ]
                        }
                
                
                JSON.parse
                
                
                
            
            SCRIPT
            
            <script>
            
                we use them in external file, like script.js
                
                we add  <script src=script.js>  in the html or ejs file at the end
            
            
            
            LOOPS
            
               for (let i = 0; i < cars.length; i++) {
                         text += cars[i] + "<br>";
                        }
            
            
            
            
            
            GOOGLE MAPS adding
            
            
                   Simple Screenshot implementation:
                   https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OP8tK9hQNuo&ab_channel=oneminutecoder
                   
                   
                   
            
                   Typescript course 63.
                   
                   into html file:
                   <script src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key= APIKEY
                   
                   
                   npm install @types/google.maps
                   
                   
                   add this to the index.ts in the first line
                   /// <reference types="@types/google.maps" />
                   
                   
                   / actually works without cause we have no err
                   tells ts there is a global var called google and all the different functions and properties it has
                   npm install --save @types/google.maps
                   
                   
                   
            
            GLOBAL VARIABLE
            
                  doesnt need to be extra imported or exported (import / export statements)
                  is avaiable everywhere in out project

            
                 
                 
                 
                 
                 
                 
                 
           
                 
            
            
            
